    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='Based on the provided excerpts from the S-1 prospectus preamble, here is the breakdown of the exchange ratios, consideration paid, fair value accounting, and the $2.947 billion cash payment regarding the xAI Merger:\n\n### 1. Exchange Ratio\nThe filing establishes a fixed, pre-2026 Stock Split exchange ratio of **0.1433** for converting xAI equity into SpaceX equity, alongside specific ratios for the X Merger:\n*   **xAI Preferred Stock:** Series A-1, B, C, D, and E ("Low Vote") converted into **0.1433** shares of SpaceX Class A Common Stock. Series A ("High Vote") converted into **0.1433** shares of SpaceX Class B Common Stock.\n*   **xAI Common Stock:** All classes (Class A, Class B, and Limited Voting) converted into SpaceX Common Stock at the **0.1433** ratio.\n*   **xAI Equity Awards & Warrants:** Options, RSUs, RSAs, and customer warrants converted into SpaceX equivalents at the **0.1433** ratio. (For options, the exercise price was divided by 0.1433).\n*   **X Holdings Corp. (X Merger):** X Common Stock converted into xAI Common Stock at a ratio of **2.776** (which then subsequently converts to SpaceX at the 0.1433 ratio). X.AI Corp. common and preferred stock converted at a **1.000** ratio into xAI equivalents.\n*   *Fractional Shares:* Fractional SpaceX shares were rounded *up* to the nearest whole number for xAI preferred/common stock, but rounded *down* for X Common Stock.\n\n### 2. Consideration Paid\nTo effectuate the xAI Merger on February 2, 2026, SpaceX paid the following consideration to xAI stockholders:\n*   **Stock Issuance:** SpaceX issued **321,681,643 shares of Class A Common Stock** and **121,683,400 shares of Class B Common Stock** as partial consideration. \n    * *Note:* This Class A issuance includes 3,798,039 shares issued to Tesla, which converted Tesla\'s prior $2 billion investment in xAI Series E Preferred Stock into SpaceX Class A stock following regulatory approval.\n*   **Cash Election Option:** "Eligible service providers" holding xAI Series A Preferred Stock or xAI Class A/B Common Stock were granted the right to elect cash instead of stock, priced at **$75.46 per share** (on a pre-2026 Stock Split basis).\n*   **Cash Payment:** A massive lump-sum cash payment (detailed in section 4 below).\n\n### 3. Fair Value of Consideration\n*   **No Fair Value Recast (Common Control Accounting):** The filing explicitly states that because Elon Musk held a controlling financial/majority voting interest in SpaceX, xAI, and X, the mergers were accounted for as **reorganizations of entities under common control**. Therefore, the entities were combined at their **historical carrying amounts**, *not* fair value. No new goodwill or intangible assets were recorded, and historical financial statements were retrospectively combined rather than undergoing a fair-value purchase price allocation.\n*   **CEO Award Fair Value:** The only specific "fair value" calculations provided in the text relate to the grant date fair value assumptions for the CEO\'s xAI performance stock award (using an expected term of 10.0 years, volatility of 45%–55%, risk-free rate of 4.06%, and 0.00% dividend yield).\n\n### 4. The $2.947 Billion Cash Payment\n*   **The Payment:** Pursuant to the terms of the xAI Merger on February 2, 2026, alongside the issuance of Class A and Class B stock, SpaceX **paid $2,947 million ($2.947 billion) in cash** to holders of xAI Common Stock and Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock.\n*   **Context & Accounting Impact:** This cash outlay was a core component of the merger consideration. It likely corresponds to the cash elections made by eligible service providers (who opted for the $75.46/share payout), the cashless exercise mechanics of certain warrants, or other specific merger agreement provisions requiring cash settlement. \n*   **Balance Sheet Reflection:** In the *Consolidated Statement of Changes in Equity*, this massive cash outflow appears to be heavily reflected in the line item **"Repurchase of common stock pursuant to xAI Merger,"** which shows a **$(2,413) million** reduction to Additional Paid-in Capital and Total Shareholders\' Equity, representing the accounting treatment of cash paid out to retiring xAI equity holders.',
