        output='## Historical Information No Longer Observable Under Common-Control Accounting vs. Purchase Accounting\n\nThe SpaceX S-1 retrospectively recasts all historical periods under **common-control accounting** (ASC 805-50) because Elon Musk held a controlling/majority voting interest in SpaceX, xAI, and X Holdings during all periods presented. This treatment fundamentally differs from purchase accounting (ASC 805 acquisition method) and renders the following categories of historical information **no longer observable**:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Fair Value of Acquired Net Assets\nUnder purchase accounting, the acquirer must remeasure all acquired assets and assumed liabilities to their **acquisition-date fair values** (the "step-up" or "step-down"). Under common-control accounting, the net assets of xAI and X were combined into SpaceX\'s consolidated financials at their **historical carrying amounts** (book values). Investors cannot observe what the fair value of xAI\'s or X\'s net assets—such as AI infrastructure, the Grok model, the X platform, user data, or spectrum rights—would have been at the merger dates.\n\n### 2. Merger-Generated Goodwill\nPurchase accounting would have recognized **goodwill** equal to the excess of the purchase consideration over the fair value of identifiable net assets. Given that SpaceX paid $2.947 billion in cash plus 321.7 million Class A shares and 121.7 million Class B shares (pre-split) for xAI, a substantial goodwill balance would likely have been created. The filing explicitly states: **"No new goodwill or other intangible assets have been recorded"** as a result of the mergers. The $11,681 million in goodwill on the consolidated balance sheet as of March 31, 2026 (of which $11,166 million is in the AI segment) reflects only **pre-existing goodwill** from X\'s original 2022 take-private acquisition—not any incremental goodwill from the SpaceX/xAI or xAI/X mergers.\n\n### 3. New Intangible Asset Recognition\nPurchase accounting would have required the identification and fair-value measurement of **acquired intangible assets** such as customer relationships, developed technology (Grok LLM), trade names, and the X platform\'s user base. Under common-control accounting, no new intangible assets were recognized. The existing intangible asset balances (including the X brand, which was impaired by $3,775 million in 2023 and reclassified as finite-lived with a 5-year useful life) reflect X\'s original purchase accounting from 2022, not any fresh measurement.\n\n### 4. Purchase Price Allocation\nNo **purchase price allocation** was performed. Under purchase accounting, the acquirer must disclose a detailed allocation of consideration to each major class of assets acquired and liabilities assumed, including contingent liabilities. This allocation—which would have revealed the implied value of xAI\'s AI compute infrastructure, X\'s user base and advertising platform, and other key assets—is entirely absent.\n\n### 5. Standalone Pre-Merger SpaceX Financials\nBecause the consolidated financials are retrospectively recast to combine SpaceX, xAI, and X **for all periods presented**, investors **cannot isolate standalone SpaceX-only historical results** (i.e., the Space and Connectivity segments operating without xAI/X). Every historical income statement, balance sheet, and cash flow statement in the filing reflects the combined entity. While segment-level disclosures partially mitigate this (Space, Connectivity, and AI segments are reported separately), the consolidated top-line figures, tax provisions, debt balances, and cash flows are fully commingled for all historical periods.\n\n### 6. Standalone xAI and X Financial Statements\nThe filing explicitly states that **separate financial statements for xAI and X are not provided**. Under purchase accounting, the acquired entity\'s standalone pre-acquisition financials would typically be filed (or incorporated by reference) as part of the registration statement. Here, because the entities are treated as always having been combined, no standalone xAI or X financial statements exist in the filing.\n\n### 7. Historical Related-Party Transactions Between the Entities\nAll historical transactions between SpaceX, xAI, and X that were previously classified as **related-party transactions** have been **retroactively eliminated in consolidation**. This means investors cannot observe:\n- The scale, pricing, or terms of any inter-company service agreements, data-sharing arrangements, or cost-sharing agreements that existed before the formal mergers\n- Whether any entity was subsidizing another (e.g., whether SpaceX was providing below-market launch services to xAI/X, or whether X was providing below-market compute or data access to xAI)\n- The volume and nature of cash flows between the entities\n\n### 8. Implied Acquisition Premium/Discount\nUnder purchase accounting, the relationship between the purchase consideration and the fair value of net assets acquired reveals the **acquisition premium** (or bargain purchase gain). Because no fair value measurement of net assets was performed, and because the consideration included both cash ($2.947 billion) and equity (443.4 million pre-split shares at an implied $75.46/share for cash-election purposes), investors cannot calculate the implied premium or discount SpaceX paid to acquire xAI.\n\n### 9. xAI Preferred Stock on an As-Converted Historical Basis\nAs a specific exception within the recast, **xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock** is presented in its historical legal form for all periods prior to the February 2026 merger—it is **not** retrospectively recast on an as-converted-to-SpaceX-equity basis. This means investors cannot observe what the consolidated capital structure would have looked like on an as-converted basis in prior periods; the conversion is only recognized prospectively in Q1 2026.\n\n---\n\n### Summary Table\n\n| Information Category | Purchase Accounting | Common-Control Accounting (This Filing) |\n|---|---|---|\n| Asset/liability fair values at merger | Observable (step-up/step-down) | **Not observable** (historical carrying amounts) |\n| Merger-generated goodwill | Recognized and disclosed | **Not recorded** |\n| New intangible assets | Identified and measured at FV | **Not recorded** |\n| Purchase price allocation | Detailed disclosure required | **Not performed** |\n| Standalone acquirer (SpaceX) pre-merger financials | Preserved unchanged | **Not separable** (fully recast) |\n| Standalone target (xAI/X) financials | Filed or incorporated | **Not provided** |\n| Pre-merger related-party transactions | Visible until acquisition date | **Retroactively eliminated** |\n| Acquisition premium/discount | Calculable | **Not calculable** |\n\n---\n\n**Sources:**\n{\n  "sources": [\n    {\n      "url": "https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1181412/000162828026036936/spaceexplorationtechnologi.htm",\n      "name": "SpaceX S-1 Registration Statement (filed May 20, 2026)"\n    }\n  ]\n}',
        error=None,
